name: Tamaraw "Dwarf Buffalo"
description:
Tamaraw “Dwarf Buffalo”, is a critically endangered animal and one of the endemic species in the Philippines. It features shiny black hair, backward-facing horns, and a height no taller than a kindergartener but has tempered and will readily wield its horns against intruders, a behavior called “tusking”.
In Philippine folklore, Tamaraw is the fastest and stronger animal in the forest and he was a short temper. In the forest there is a small rat named Daga, he is always angry with Daga. One day Tamaraw is trapped in the forest, and no one wants to help him because of his attitude. Then Daga saw Tamaraw and help him escape from the trap. 

It reminds us that we cannot save ourselves, time will come our enemy will save us.  

Source: https://www.zenrooms.com/blog/post/endangered-species-in-the-philippines/
